Verify the HAL stream components reject an invalid cfg pin type.

Re-expressed for gomc: the classic test used the Python hal.stream(...,"xx")
binding and asserted it raised on the invalid cfg 'x'.  gomc removed the embedded
Python hal.stream binding, so the same validation is exercised by loading the
filestream cmod with sample_cfg=xx and confirming the load fails (the cmod's
hal_stream_parse_cfg rejects any type that is not f/b/u/s).
